# Spring Boot Employee Management System

 For testing APIs, a straightforward CRUD application was created with Spring Boot, MySQL, JPA, and Postman.

 ## Technologies Employed: Java 17, Spring Boot, and Spring Data  Postman, Maven, MySQL Database, and JPA

 ## Features: Add Employee; Get Employee by ID; Get All Employees; Update Employee; Delete Employee

 ## Endpoints for APIs

 | Description | Endpoint | Method | -----| ----------+-| -------------| | POST | /employee/add | Add new employee | | GET | /employee/get/{id} | Get employee by ID | | GET | /employee/all | Get all employees | | PUT | /employee/update/{id} | Update employee | | DELETE | /employee/delete/{id} | Delete employee |

 ## How to Operate
 1. Establish the employee_db MySQL database
 2. Update application.properties
 3. Launch the primary class  
 4. Test APIs using Postman

